From 77b6c221e5bf26c2fc2180951119c7a052fca1f3 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Miroslav Zagorac <mzagorac@haproxy.com>
Date: Wed, 15 Apr 2026 21:16:01 +0200
Subject: [PATCH 2/5] [EXPORTERS] Add MaybeSpawnBackgroundThread() to OTLP HTTP
 exporters

The curl HTTP client's background thread is started lazily on the first
call to Session::SendRequest().  This delays thread creation until the
first batch export, which may happen seconds after program start.

Added a virtual MaybeSpawnBackgroundThread() method to the base HttpClient
interface (default no-op) and marked the existing curl implementation as
an override.  Exposed the method through OtlpHttpClient and all three OTLP
HTTP exporter classes (traces, metrics, logs) so callers can pre-spawn the
thread immediately after construction.
